HEADWORD: Langarey
<hw>Lan`ga*rey"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of numerous species of long-winged, shrikelike birds of
Australia and the East Indies, of the genus <gen>Artamus</gen>, and
allied genera; called also <altname>wood swallow</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Langate</ent>⟦br⟧
